message: I extend to you my warm wishes for a healthy & Happy New Year! I look forward to continuing my service to the constituents of New Jersey's First United States Congressional District in 2017.

I was honored to participate in the Pine Hill, New Jersey Council Reorganization meeting January 2, 2017. Congratulations to Councilmen Terence Burke & Charles Warrington who took the oath of office today.
Congratulations to newly sworn-in Berlin Township New Jersey Council members Marion Bodanza and Chris Morris. Photos: from the Township's Reorganization Meeting January 2, 2017.
It was an honor administering the oath of office to Oaklyn, New Jersey council members Robert Skowronek and Krista Egan at the Borough's reorganization meeting January 2, 2017.

Congratulations to Washington Township, Gloucester County, New Jersey's new Mayor Joann Gattinelli & council members Dana Pasqualone & Joseph Perry. And, congratulations are in order for the new leader of the Washington Township Police Department (Gloucester County) New Jersey, Chief Pat Gurcsik, sworn in by Senator Fred H. Madden.

Thank you to the public servants of Brooklawn, New Jersey serving on the Borough's Council-- Greg Gilbert & Patrick Moses, taking the oath of office, as administered by New Jersey General Assemblyman Arthur Barclay at the Borough's reorganization meeting January 2, 2017.
Congratulations & thank you to Lourdes Health System & Cooper University Health Care for raising awareness about organ & tissue donation.

As a lifelong resident of South Jersey, it’s an honor to represent the First United States Congressional District.  Creating jobs and fighting for working families remains my top priority. I will continue to press the new administration to renegotiate bad trade deals. We need fair trade that creates jobs here at home – not just free trade that ships jobs overseas.  We must also come together to invest in Southern New Jersey's infrastructure. Strengthening our region’s ports, railways, roads and bridges, as well as our energy infrastructure, will create jobs and position our economy for the next century of progress. To fill those jobs, we must expand affordable educational opportunities for every South Jersey family, especially at the county colleges and apprenticeship programs  – where I began my own career as an electrician.  And providing top-quality services for our residents will always be job one. My office is ready to help the people of South Jersey with any problem they may face, from receiving veteran’s benefits to resolving Medicare and Social Security Administration issues.

Gloucester County NJ Deputy Director Freeholder Joe Chila administered the oath of office to Antonio "Tony" Chila at the Greenwich Township New Jersey Reorganization Meeting. Also sworn-in to office: Councilman Vincent Giovannetti. Congratulations to both members of Council.
Congratulations to Audubon Park Borough New Jersey Council members Dennis Delangowski & Gloria Jones on their new, 3 year terms serving the constituents of the Borough.
Progress to report on a major project in Camden, New Jersey. Holtec International Marlton Nj will start moving into its new headquarters starting next month. The future has arrived!

It’s an honor to represent New Jersey’s working families on the Education and Workforce Committee. This is a continuation of my lifelong fight to defend hard working men and women and make certain that every person has the dignity of a good paying job.  I’ve built bridges and buildings across South Jersey, and now I’m working to build bridges in Washington — by working with both sides of the aisle to fight for policies that put American workers first.

A proud moment as I take the oath as a Member of the 115th United States Congress with my wife, Andrea by my side and Speaker Paul Ryan administered the ceremonial oath. I'm eager to continue my advocacy for the hard working families of Southern New Jersey as Congress gets back to work.

A special thanks to the steady leadership of Deptford Township - Municipal/ Deptford, New Jersey under the guidance of Mayor Paul Medany & Council as they start 2017 with their reorganization meeting. Councilman Wayne Love recalled a special moment in the Township in 2016-the dedication of the Deptford Post Office In Memory of 1st LT Sal Corma, legislation I authored & sponsored in United States Congress.

Linda Hall & Tina Lomanno take the oath of office in Stratford, New Jersey. Camden County Government Freeholder Director Lou Cappelli and New Jersey General Assemblywoman Pamela Lampitt were on hand to swear-in the Council members. I thank all for their service to the Borough.

With Gloucester County NJ Freeholder Jim Jefferson offering inspirational words, Paulsboro Borough/ Paulsboro, New Jersey leaders convened for their reorganization meeting, swearing in Councilman John Giovannitti & Councilman Eric Ditonno. Paulsboro Mayor Gary Stevenson, Sr. reflected on 2016 & looked ahead at what we all hope will be the first ship to come in to the Port of Paulsboro in the new year!

Voorhees Township/ Voorhees Township, New Jersey Mayor Michael Mignogna, Deputy Mayor Jason Ravitz & Committeeman Michael Friedman took their oaths at the Township's reorganization meeting--ready to take on the business of local government in 2017. I look forward to working with all of them in the new year.

A "who's who" of Camden County Government leaders on hand to witness the oaths taken by Robert Farrell & Michael Root at the Borough of Runnemede, NJ/ Runnemede, New Jersey reorganization meeting. Among the guests: New Jersey General Assemblywoman Patricia Jones, Sheriff Whip Wilson, and Runnemede native, Freeholder Bill Moen.

My path to United States Congress began at Camden County College & in an IBEW apprenticeship program. On the House Committee on Education and the Workforce, I’m going to make it my mission to support affordable education alternatives, including access to county colleges and apprenticeship programs. We must invest now in preparing the next generation of tradesmen and women to fulfill tomorrow’s jobs.

Congratulations to Council Members Anthony Perno & Griffin Kidd who took the oath of office at the Merchantville NJ / Merchantville, New Jersey Reorganization Meeting with Camden County Government Deputy Freeholder Director Ed McDonnell & Carmen Rodriguez administering the oaths.
I join with more than 170 colleagues in United States Congress calling for an independent investigation into foreign interference in the U.S. elections.

I was proud to administer the oath of office to Gloucester County NJ Deputy Director Freeholder Joe Chila, while my former colleague, New Jersey Senate President Steve Sweeney administered the oath to Freeholder Director Robert Damminger. Congratulations to Freeholders Dan Christy Freeholder & Frank DiMarco on a new, 3 year term serving constituents of Gloucester County!

It was a pleasure swearing-in Borough of Barrington/ Barrington, New Jersey Councilman Mike Beach. Also taking the oath at the Borough's reorganization--Wayne Robenolt. And, this meeting was bittersweet, as Council thanked Maureen Therese for her years of service. I was proud to present her with a United States Congressional Proclamation for her commitment to the constituents of Barrington.

I'm honored to continue my work safeguarding the United States with my reappointment to the House Armed Services Committee Democrats in United States Congress. This critical role enables me to continue to fight prominently for New Jersey's military & veteran families and advocate for the future of Joint Base McGuire-Dix-Lakehurst, critical to our nation's security & New Jersey's economy.

He's not just a Mayor--he's a life saver! Paulsboro Mayor Gary Stevenson, Sr. saved a woman from a burning home in Paulsboro, New Jersey. The Mayor is also a volunteer with Paulsboro Volunteer Fire Association #1 / Paulsboro Fire/Rescue. Mayor Gary Stevenson-a Southern New Jersey hero!
Congratulations are in order for Councilwoman Cindy McCoy as she takes the oath of office at Borough of Hi-Nella's / Hi-Nella, New Jersey's Reorganization Meeting.

Two special moments in Westville, New Jersey as Council members Paul Mailley & Donna Moan take the oath of office in the Gloucester County NJ community. Congratulations to both. I look forward to working with them & continue serving all the constituents of Southern New Jersey.

Grateful for the opportunity to meet with Secretary of the Air Force Deborah Lee James of the United States Air Force to advocate for the new Boeing KC-46 tanker planes to be stationed at New Jersey's Joint Base McGuire-Dix-Lakehurst. In the last United States Congress, I successfully fought to protect the KC-10 refueling tanker planes at the Base. The base is ideal for the next generation of tankers-the KC-46. The aircraft would provide greater certainty for our national security, for future generations of New Jerseyans & the State's economy.

I'm proud to announce the United States Air Force has selected Joint Base McGuire-Dix-Lakehurst for the next generation of Boeing Company air refueling tanker, the Boeing KC-46 Pegasus- critical to United States national security, thousands of New Jersey's enlisted and civilian employees, and the State's economy.
Gloucester Township, New Jersey begins 2017 with its reorganization meeting. I look forward to working with Mayor David Mayer & Council in the New Year!

Camden County Government Freeholders Ed McDonnell & Carmen Rodriguez are tireless advocates for constituents of Camden County, New Jersey. And so their new terms as Freeholders are well-deserved. I congratulate them and look forward to the work ahead for our community.

Proud of my hometown, Pennsauken, New Jersey and grateful for the dedicated public servants of the community. Congratulations to Committeeman Rick Taylor as he begins a new term serving the Township that will always be home to me.

With my former New Jersey Senate colleague, New Jersey Senate President Steve Sweeney administering the oaths of office, West Deptford Township/ West Deptford, New Jersey Committee Members James Robinson & Megan Kerr were sworn-in at the Township's reorganization meeting. The Committee Members selected Denice Maryanski DiCarlo for another term as Mayor. Congratulations to all!

Talk about service! Logan Township, New Jersey/ Logan Township, NJ Councilwoman Doris Hall began her 5th term on Council at the Township's reorganization meeting. Mayor Frank Minor administered the oath to Councilwoman Hall and Councilman Art Smith. I thank these leaders for their commitment to this great Gloucester County NJ community.

My official statement after receiving classified United States Congressional briefing from Office of the Director of National Intelligence James R. Clapper, FBI – Federal Bureau of Investigation Director James Comey, Central Intelligence Agency (CIA) Director John Brennan and NSA - National Security Agency Director Michael Rogers on Russian hacking of 2016 election.

They don't call the Borough of Magnolia/ Magnolia, New Jersey "One Square Mile of Friendliness" for nothing. They ushered in 2017 by swearing in Council members Paula Bonamassa & Tony DePrince with some Philadelphia Mummers Parade flair. Congratulations to Fire Chief Paul Wolf for being selected as Magnolia's employee of the year.

Glassboro New Jersey begins 2017 by celebrating the swearing-in ceremonies for Councilmen George Cassabone, Sr. &  Ed Malandro. I extend to them and all the leadership of Glassboro NJ/ Glassboro, New Jersey my warm wishes for a fruitful New Year!

Gibbsboro, New Jersey Council Members Mitchell Brown & Gerard Bonsall are ready to take on 2017! Congratulations to them on their new terms in office, as celebrated at Gibbsboro's reorganization meeting!

With New Jersey Senate/Senator Nilsa I. Cruz-Perez administering the oaths of office, Wood-Lynne, New Jersey/ Woodlynne Borough Councilmen Joseph Chukwueke & William Valle vow to advocate on behalf of the Borough in the New Year & beyond. I thank them for their service!

I'm proud to represent Wenonah, New Jersey / Borough of Wenonah in United States Congress. And, I extend  my gratitude to Councilmen Phil Kaeferle & Don Cox as they mark the beginning of their terms at the Borough's Reorganization Meeting.

I'm determined to stand up and stand for the constituents of New Jersey & the United States with my colleagues in United States Congress to protect the Affordable Care Act from repeal. It's a proven life saver, and I'm steadfast in my commitment & pledge to preserve it for the millions who count on it. #DayofAction

On this Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr./ Martin Luther King Jr. Day of Service, I'm proud to be part of the effort to preserve a Southern New Jersey landmark--a Camden, New Jersey property that was once home to Dr. King in the 1950s.

On this Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr./ Martin Luther King Jr. Day of Service, we continue to be inspired by the words, wisdom & peaceful actions of the late civil rights leader to work toward positive, meaningful change & equality for all.

I was honored to be welcomed to Holy Eucharist Cherry Hill in Cherry Hill Township for the Knights of Columbus tribute breakfast in honor of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. I was proud to honor Jim Peeler for his contributions to our community!

Congratulations to Somerdale, New Jersey Councilmen Ed Kain & Dave Alexander as they begin new terms serving the Borough. Both members of Council took the oaths of office at the Borough's reorganization meeting.

It's been one of my favorite eateries for years. Now, its reputation for delicious food is spreading. See what the New York Post is saying about Donkey's Place in Camden, New Jersey. Yep, they make some of the BEST sandwiches in the whole United States!

I have great concern over Betsy Devos’s nomination to lead the U.S. Department of Education, an agency many Republicans have pushed to eliminate.   Serving on the Committee on Education and Workforce Democrats, I’ll fight to hold the next education secretary accountable, to make higher education more affordable and to ensure every student has access to a great public education.

On behalf of a Lindenwold, New Jersey American Gold Star Mothers, National (Official) member, Jacquelyn Dixon, I encourage veterans, active military & friends to attend the open house of the Spc. Anthony J. Dixon & Friends Center February 4, 2017. This facility, named after a U.S. Army hero killed in action in Iraq in 2004, will serve as a valuable resource to Southern New Jersey's veteran & military community.

Gloucester City, New Jersey ushered in 2017 with Council members Hutchinson, Parry & Keating taking the oaths of office, as administered by New Jersey Senate/Senator Nilsa Cruz-Perez & Camden County Government Freeholder Bill Moen. Congratulations to the members of Council and best wishes for the new year ahead!

It was an honor to join New Jersey Senate/ Senator Fred H. Madden to administer the oaths of office to council members James Casey & Ray Bider at the Bellmawr, New Jersey/ Borough of Bellmawr reorganization meeting. I look forward to working with Mayor Frank Filipek & Council in 2017 & beyond!

As home to Red Bank Battlefield, National Park, New Jersey is a Southern New Jersey historic treasure. I am grateful to members of the Borough's Council including Dennis Burke & Joy Hibbs as they begin new terms to serve constituents, after taking their oaths of office, administered by New Jersey General Assemblyman  John Burzichelli.

I'm honored & humbled to be reappointed to a leadership position as Assistant Whip in the 115th United States Congress. I look forward to working with my colleagues on issues to ensure effective government leadership for the constituents of New Jersey and the United States.

Help for New Jersey constituents experiencing difficulty paying their utility bills. There are programs in place to help through the Affordable Housing Alliance. Also, my staff can assist constituents with utility issues. Call my office in Cherry Hill at 856-427-7000.

Then Glassboro State College was known as New Jersey's Teachers' College. Today, Rowan University is a world-class higher education & research facility with a remarkable record of success. The latest jewel on campus, the gleaming new $63 million Rowan University - Rohrer College of Business facility. As a newly appointed Member of the United States Congressional House Committee on Education and the Workforce, I'm more determined than ever to ensure South Jersey students have access to quality, affordable education.

I was honored to participate in the  Haddon Heights, New Jersey Reorganization Meeting as Councilman Bryan Schroeder and Councilwoman Bernadette Russell took their oaths of office. I extend to them my every good wish as they help lead the Borough in the new year!

If the Affordable Care Act is repealed, millions of New Jerseyans could lose their insurance. They're not just numbers — they're real people.  We're sharing their stories and standing with them to save health care.

I'm proud to stand with women from across our state and around the country to defend women's rights, human rights and civil rights at the march in Trenton today.   New Jerseyans marching in DC are invited to stop by our open office at 1531 Longworth today for any help or assistance you may need while visiting our nation's capital.

Congratulations to Township of Monroe/ Monroe Township, Gloucester County, New Jersey Councilmen Marvin Dilks, Rich DiLucia, Ron Garbowski & Joe Marino as they take their oaths of office at the Township's reorganization meeting. I wish you all the best as you lead the Township in the new year!

A new year brings new terms in office for East Greenwich Township, New Jersey Councilmen James Philbin & Stephen Bottiglieri. I wish them and the entire leadership of the Township all my best in 2017.

An emotional moment at Lindenwold, New Jersey's reorganization as New Jersey Senate/ Senator Fred H. Madden & New Jersey General Assemblywoman Gabriela Mosquera presented an honor to American Gold Star Mothers, National (Official) Jacquelyn Dixon in tribute to her late son, U.S. Army Specialist Anthony J. Dixon, killed in action in Iraq in 2004. The Borough's reorganization continued with the swearing-in ceremonies for councilmen Joe Stripoli & Joseph DiDomenico. Congratulations to them!

I joined with women, for women at the Women's March on NJ - Women United, Together We Rise - Trenton with United States Congressional colleagues Reps. Bonnie Watson Coleman & Frank Pallone Jr. + New Jersey General Assemblywomen Pamela Lampitt & Patricia Jones + women from across New Jersey as we take a stand for the rights of our wives, mothers, sisters, daughters, granddaughters, and all the women in our lives. #WomensMarchonNJ

I'm proud to represent the historic Borough of Lawnside, New Jersey in United States Congress. Join me in congratulating Councilmen Steve Pollard & Rob Lee as they take the oaths of office for their terms at the Borough's reorganization. Thanks to Sheriff Whip Wilson & New Jersey General Assemblywoman Patricia Jones for administering the oaths of office.

It seems all references to LGBTQ issues have been removed from website for The White House/The White House (Official)/The Trump White House. Check out www.WhiteHouse.gov and see for yourself. As a long-time advocate for the LGBTQ community, I want to reassure my LGBTQ friends that I will continue to stand for them and their rights, and I expect the same of our new administration.

My statement after President Donald J. Trump issued executive order withdrawing the United States from the Trans-Pacific Partnership negotiations. Together, we must work together for better trade deals for the hardworking families of the United States & New Jersey.

My official statement after President Donald J. Trump reinstated the Mexico City Policy, also known as the Global gag rule-- which limits funding to Non-Governmental Organizations which provide vital health care & family planning services to the poorest families in the world.

I was grateful for the opportunity to address Southern New Jersey business & industry leaders at the Southern New Jersey Development Council's Public Policy Series at Adelphia Restaurant / Nightclub in Deptford, New Jersey. Among the topics of discussion: my role in the 115th United States Congress & the issues critical to constituents of NJ & the United States: jobs, education & national security.
Congratulations to Borough OfBerlin/Berlin, New Jersey Councilmen James Pierce & Daniel MacDonnell as they start the new year by taking the oath of office!

Borough of Woodbury Heights/Woodbury Heights, New Jersey Council members William Packer & Cara Witasick begin 2017 & their 3-year terms in office with a swearing-in ceremony at the Borough's reorganization meeting. I wish them and all the leadership of the Borough all my best in the year ahead.

Check out my recent interview in ELECTRICAL CONTRACTOR Magazine/ECmag.com--the article is entitled: "Electrician to Elected Official," and chronicles my journey from being a member of IBEW/ IBEW local 351 to becoming a Member of United States Congress.

I continue to take a stand in United States Congress for women by voting against House Republicans' latest attack on women. I believe women have the right to make their own health care decisions. It appears House Republicans don’t believe they deserve that respect.

The 2016 election showed it’s more important now than ever that House Democrats fight for working-class Americans. Serving on the United States Congressional Steering and Policy Committees of the United States House of Representatives is an opportunity to help shape our party’s agenda in Congress on issues important to Southern New Jersey & working families.

Friday, January 27, 2017 is International Holocaust Remembrance Day. During World War II, countries across Europe allowed themselves to be ruled by fear of those who were different than them. I believe today in America, we are stronger because we know we have to look out for one another, including those who are different than us. #WeRemember

I'm proud to announce this year's nominees to the United States service academies. 28 Southern New Jersey students received my nomination to the United States Naval Academy, West Point - The U.S. Military Academy, US Air Force Academy (Official) & United States Merchant Marine Academy. Join me in congratulating these students on their nominations!

We are a nation of immigrants with a Constitution that protects religious freedoms. We must maintain those values to keep our nation safe, but this executive order, signed on Holocaust Remembrance Day, does the opposite. Amid widespread confusion & protests this weekend, I'm calling for answers from administration officials & proper legal representation for all those affected. My staff & I are in touch with Philadelphia International Airport & Newark Liberty International Airport. Please contact me if your family needs assistance.  https://norcross.house.gov/contact

Today, I joined with hundreds of demonstrators to stand up for our shared values. We all agree we need to keep our nation safe — but this executive order does not accomplish that goal or represent who we are as Americans.

28 Southern New Jersey students have earned nominations to the United States service academies. As a Member of United States Congress, I have the honor of nominating them to the United States Naval Academy, West Point - The U.S. Military Academy, US Air Force Academy (Official) & United States Merchant Marine Academy. The nominees are from the following schools: Eastern Regional High School, Cherry Hill High School East, Washington Township High School, Haddonfield Memorial High School, Camden County Technical Schools, Haddon Township High School, Sterling High School (New Jersey), Highland Regional High School, Williamstown High School, Winslow Township High School, Camden Catholic High School, The King's Christian School, Audubon High School, Gloucester County Institute of Technology (GCIT), Triton Regional High School (New Jersey) & Rutgers University New Brunswick.

Amid widespread confusion and protests over the weekend, I'm calling for answers from administration officials and proper legal representation for all those affected. My staff and I are in touch with the Philadelphia International Airport & Newark Liberty International Airport, please contact me if your family needs assistance at 856-427-7000.

I was proud to join with constituents at the Katz JCC in Cherry Hill Township who generously volunteered their time for the 2017 Super Sunday to once again raise hundreds of thousands of dollars for the good works performed by the Jewish Federation of Southern New Jersey. Thank you to all who answered the call.

We cannot simply accept any attempts to sabotage the Affordable Care Act–especially when there is still so much good to be done. Don’t forget, you still have time to #GetCovered before the ACA enrollment deadline tonight (1/31/17). SIGN UP by clicking on the link below.

Where are the jobs? I spent my life in the building trades, first as an electrician, then as a union leader. Many working men and women voted for President Trump because they believed him when he promised to rebuild our infrastructure, create jobs, and raise wages. But in his first speech to Congress, Trump only paid lip service to infrastructure investment without offering any details on creating new jobs.   Democrats have a plan to invest $1 trillion in infrastructure, updating our roads, bridges and energy grid to prepare our nation for a new century of growth. It would create 15 million good-paying jobs over the next 10 years. Now it’s time for President Trump to present a real jobs plan for our nation. Until then, America's families are asking, ‘Where are the jobs?’

This Tuesday, Clarifi will host a Homeownership Workshop in South Jersey. Homeownership is a dream for many, and Clarifi is a nonprofit organization dedicated to helping you achieve it. Click below for more information!
Exciting news for the Battleship New Jersey and the Camden Waterfront.
I hope you'll join us for our next community town hall with Camden County Government on Monday, March 6! Click below to register in advance.
My reaction to President Trump's joint address. Where are the jobs? Where's the infrastructure plan? Talk is cheap. It's time to act like president!

Proud to lead 12 of my colleagues, from both sides of the aisle and across the country, in a letter to President Trump detailing the infrastructure investments we expect him to include in any jobs bill.
I'm calling on the president to present Congress with an infrastructure plan that rebuilds our country, creates jobs and raises wages.

The attorney general – the highest law enforcement official in the country, in charge of federal investigators and prosecutors – must be beyond reproach. At the very least, Attorney General Jeff Sessions lied under oath. At the very worst, Sessions could be involved in covering up Russian interference with our election.   We cannot have an attorney general who is influenced by his own conflicts of interests or a situation where he faces a possible investigation by the FBI, a department he oversees. To restore faith in our nation’s institutions, President Donald Trump must immediately call for Sessions’ resignation.
Getting set up for a high tech @njtvnewsroom Skype interview.

The demolition of the Hugg-Harrison-Glover House is an injustice for all those in the community working to save this landmark and a loss for South Jersey history. We’ve been fighting to negotiate a compromise that would preserve this historic building and allow Direct Connection to move forward. I’m deeply disappointed the New Jersey Department of Transportation destroyed the Hugg-House without warning, despite our ongoing work to save the home.

It's been a busy week in the nation's capital and in South Jersey. I'm fighting to protect democracy, to invest in infrastructure and to denounce antisemitism. Click below for more information on how I'm working for you in Washington.

President Trump's new travel ban is a distinction without much of a difference. His executive order still blocks Syrian children, Iranian doctors and even Iraqis who helped our troops now seeking to come here as refugees. The president is more focused on saving this failed policy than taking the advice of our military and intelligence experts to help keep our country safe.
Live coverage of Camden County Town Hall in Borough of Bellmawr, NJ.
I'm fighting for our fair share and to keep our community safe.
It's an honor to work with such courageous women. Proud to stand with them on the Capitol steps to mark a #DayWithoutWomen & #InternationalWomensDay!
On this International Women's Day, we're standing up for women's health care and equal rights!
I'm inspired by the millennials, the next generation of Jersey leaders, who come to Washington to speak with me about the issues most important to them.
Under the Republican Pay-More-For-Less Health Care bill, seniors and working families will pay more while trust-fund millionaires get a tax cut. I'm fighting to stop repeal and to save our care.
Thankful we have the Gloucester County NAACP in our community. They're working to protect civil rights and to eliminate racial hatred.

This isn't a plan to replace the Affordable Care Act, it's a plan to kill the ACA. The Republican plan will cost working families more and hurt seniors -- all while providing a huge tax cut for trust-fund billionaires.

Every family knows their personal budget reflects their priorities. The same is true for the federal government’s budget, and President Trump’s exposes his true priorities – more help for the billionaire class at the expense of working Americans.  The president’s budget slashes funding for health, safety, and environmental programs in our communities, and cuts vital programs like Meals on Wheels for local seniors. Worst of all, this budget doesn’t invest in infrastructure or education, and it won’t create jobs for America’s families.
This week in Washington, I'm taking action to protect our health care, defend our values and protect women's rights. Read more about our work in this week's newsletter.

Based on classified briefings, it’s been clear for some time that there was foreign interference in the 2016 election. Now, Director James Comey and the FBI – Federal Bureau of Investigation are publicly acknowledging their investigation into the Donald J. Trump campaign’s alleged ties to the Russian government. While the intelligence community conducts their own probe, I renew my call for an independent, bipartisan investigation into this matter for the sake of the future of our democracy. The American people deserve the truth.

We need to stop acts of hatred with all the resources we can get our hands on--that's why I'm grateful to Governor Chris Christie for announcing new state grant opportunities to safeguard houses of worship, community centers, and non-profits in South Jersey from those who wish to inflict harm. There's no reason Southern New Jersey should be denied access to ANY funding opportunity. That's why my fight to secure federal funding & resources through FEMA Federal Emergency Management Agency will continue in earnest. I won't stop fighting for the safety, security, and well-being of ALL my constituents.

A special salute to a hometown hero. It was a great moment in Borough of Bellmawr/ Bellmawr, New Jersey when I got to honor Andrew Johnson. Andrew served the United States in the U.S. Marine Corps in Afghanistan. Here at home, his service continues with the Camden County Sheriff's Office & the Bellmawr Fire Department. Thank you for your service and selfless sacrifice!

As you may have heard, House Republicans are pushing for a vote on Thursday on their health care bill that will take away health care from millions of families. We must continue to discuss the importance of access to health care. Therefore, although I am hoping to be in the Borough of Collingswood in-person, if I am in  Washington, District of Columbia during the time of our scheduled community conversation, I will be joining the meeting by video, and will be available for question-and-answer and ensure this important conversation continues.  We will also have experts from across New Jersey to participate in this important discussion. I look forward to seeing you Thursday!

Proud to join with former Vice President Joe Biden, House Democratic Leader Nancy Pelosi and House Democrats to mark the 7th anniversary of the Affordable Care Act--which has provided health insurance to 20 million Americans. We will continue our fight to preserve the Act.

Education & awareness save lives. That's why I'm urging those at risk to be screened for Colorectal cancer. I was proud to join with cancer experts at MD Anderson Cancer Center/ MD Anderson Cancer Center At Cooper for Colorectal Cancer Awareness Month, which is observed every March. Get screened.
NA

Who says there's no "love" at the United States Capitol? OK--call it "puppy love." March 23, 2017 is National Puppy Day! Amid the stress & tension in Congress, every now and again we get a few minutes to spend some downtime with "man's best friend." Thanks to the ASPCA, Animal Planet, Humane Rescue Alliance & all who make this day possible. Remember, if you want to add a new 4-legged family member to your home, check out your local animal shelter.

We cannot turn our backs on those battling the disease of addiction. That's why I led a group of Members of Congress in a letter to President Donald J. Trump/POTUS 45 demanding a reversal of provisions in Trumpcare that would threaten coverage for drug addiction treatment. Such an act is disgraceful, as our family, friends, and love ones fall victim to this disease.

After seven years of promising, House Republicans couldn’t pass their so-called health care bill because only two groups would have benefited: millionaires and undertakers. Though I'm thankful this vote didn't happen, I remain concerned the fight to save our health care is far from over. But, I resolve to continue to fight any plan that raises costs, cuts coverage, imposes an ‘age tax’ on seniors, guts  Medicaid, and endangers Medicare.

Operation Yellow Ribbon of South Jersey was at it again... hosting a surprise welcome home ceremony at Hollywood Cafe in Borough of Woodbury Heights/Woodbury Heights, New Jersey for MSgt. Andrew DeVito who recently returned from his 4th deployment to the Middle East where he served us in the United States Air Force/ Air National Guard. When Andrew isn't serving in our military, he's protecting us at home in his role as an officer with the Washington Township Police Department (Gloucester County) New Jersey  Join me in thanking him for his service!

One of the great honors of serving as a Member of United States Congress is presenting U.S. Flags that flew over the United States Capitol. That's exactly what I did--delivering a U.S. Flag to the Camden City School District/Board-students from Woodrow Wilson High School (New Jersey)'s Junior ROTC proudly accepted the flag on the School Board's behalf.
Happening now: my small business seminar at Camden County College
America’s workers deserve safe workplaces. But instead of giving families peace of mind, Republicans are making it easier to hide safety violations. That’s wrong.

I stand with Senator Patrick Leahy, Sen. Elizabeth Warren, Senator Maggie Hassan, Sen. Cory Booker, U.S. Senator Bob Casey & others calling for pay equity for U.S. Women's National Hockey Team-As I said last year about Carli Lloyd & U.S.A. Women's National Soccer Team--women athletes shouldn't be the victims of paycheck discrimination when they're doing the same job as a man. Same goes for EVERY woman in the workforce today.  https://norcross.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/rep-norcross-renews-fight-women-s-equality-national-equal-pay-day

This is a day that shouldn't even exist. Yet, here we are marking another Equal Pay Day. Women performing the same job as a man, shouldn't be getting paid less. That's blatant discrimination and that's exactly why I support the Paycheck Fairness Act in Congress. I'll continue to fight for pay equity for ALL women.

I join with Congressman Adam Schiff calling on House Republicans Intelligence Chair, Congressman Devin Nunes to recuse himself from the Donald J. Trump-Russia investigation. The American people deserve a fair, independent investigation into this matter. The developments with the Intelligence Committee Chairman only serve as a distraction as we seek to learn the facts.

Small businesses are the backbone of our great nation. And so I was proud to offer a special seminar for Southern New Jersey small businesses & entrepreneurs at Camden County College. The event featured experts from United States Government Small Busines Administration, New Jersey Economic Development Authority, New Jersey Small Business Development Centers Network, Rutgers University—Camden, Rowan University - Rohrer College of Business, Chamber of Commerce Southern New Jersey, Enlil Communications, 10,000 Small Businesses at Community College of Philadelphia, NJMEP, and many more. I am deeply saddened by the passing of my friend, Senator Jim Whelan.   I had the honor of working with Jim for years both as a labor advocate and a fellow state legislator, and always knew him to be honest, hard working, thoughtful and sincere.   Jim will, of course, be remembered as a fierce and greatly successful advocate for Atlantic City and the entire Jersey Shore. His colleagues will also remember his dry wit, good nature and competitive spirit, especially when it came to his beloved local sports teams and the students he mentored. Most importantly, he was a devoted husband and father to his wife Kathy and son Richard.   Jim was a true gentleman, and he will be sorely missed.

On Monday, March 27, I'd like to welcome you to Camden County College-Blackwood Campus to meet with representatives from the U.S. Small Business Administration (SBA), the New Jersey Economic Development Authority (NJ EDA), and small business experts from across our region for a free seminar to help your business survive and thrive in today's economy.  To RSVP please call my office in Cherry Hill at 856-427-7000.   Small businesses are the backbone of our great nation. When small businesses succeed, America is stronger. Unfortunately, only a small percentage of new small businesses survive after their first year. Just as small businesses make their commitment to and investments in our community, I'm committed to ensuring our friends and neighbors have access to the resources they need to succeed. That's why I'm hosting an exciting, free event featuring federal resources for existing small businesses in South Jersey and entrepreneurs.
